The panel made a total of 73 recommendations but not all were accepted. CAPE TOWN - Cabinet has endorsed and supported 60 of the recommendations made by the Presidential Advisory Panel on Land Reform and Agriculture. The panel made a total of 73 recommendations but not all were accepted. Departments also had to give input as to how the recommendations would affect them. Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu explained: “Through the committee on land reform, all affected departments were asked to study the recommendations and to respond accordingly.” The various departments will provide a full briefing on the areas that were not approved.